original: LJUNGQVIST, Gunnar Natanael, Försäkringsdirektör, Ålsten, f Ockelbo 9/2 98 av kontr.prost teol dr E G L o Gertrud Jonzon, gm Solveig Bergquist. Fil kand Upps 21. Ack-vis Försäkr AB Skandia 25—27, tjman 27—31, ombudsinsp Städ Allm Brandstodsbol 31—34, bitr dir 34, v. vkst dir sed. 36, i Städ oms. Livförsäkr.bol sed. 38. Ag fastigh Ålsten. Stdsflm, stadskoll, ordf stdsflms högergr sed. 42. l:e kur G-II nation 21—23, studentkårens v ordf 24—25, styr.led Sv Försäkr.frn 34—36, led Skadeförsäkr.bol:s skiljenmd sed. 36, vkst led Finl.insaml Industria, led Finl.komm av 39—40 o 41; ordf Sthlm-Högerns frb sed. 40. Resor: Engl 32 ss Sv Försäkr.frns Ruben-sonstip mfl. Av trycket: Hist del av Försäkr AB Skandias 75-årsskrift, art i dags- och fackpress. RVO, RFinlVRO.
translated: LJUNGQVIST, Gunnar Natanael, Insurance Director, Ålsten, born in Ockelbo on February 9th, 1898, son of the district dean, doctor of theology E.G.L and Gertrud Jonzon, married to Solveig Bergquist. Bachelor's degree from Uppsala University in 1921. Joined Ack-vis Insurance Company Skandia in 1925-1927, served as an assistant manager from 1927-1931, and as an inspector for Städ Allm Brandstodsbol from 1931-1934. Became an assistant director in 1934, and then vice head of operations director since 1936 in a different insurance company called Städ oms. Livförsäkr.bol. He owned property in Ålsten. Member of the city council and chairman of the city council's conservative group since 1942. First board member of G-II Nation from 1921-1923, vice chairman of the student union from 1924-1925, board member of the Swedish Insurance Association from 1934-1936, member of the arbitration board of the insurance company Skadeförsäkr.bol since 1936, board member of the Finnish Industrial Insurance Fund, member of the Finnish Commission from 1939-1940 and 1941. Chairman of the Stockholm Conservatives' Association since 1940. Traveled to England in 1932 on the Svenska Försäkringsföreningens Rubenson scholarship. Published in the history section of the 75th anniversary publication of the insurance company Skandia, as well as in daily and professional press. Awarded the Order of the Sword (Royal Order of the Seraphim) and the Order of the Lion of Finland (Knight, First Class).

honors.name: Order of the Lion of Finland
